					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So, the sprites are NOT evaluated during the dummy scanline. I don't know about the MMC3 IRQ risings, though... I was very lazy during past days. :P</div>
<br />
<br />No, they are.  It's just impossible for sprite-0 hit or sprite overflow to happen on the prerender scanline because it's impossible for <em>any</em> sprite to be in-range on that scanline.  The lowest Y coord you can give any sprite is 0, which means it will be found in-range on scanline 0, then rendered on scanline 1.
<br />
<br />There's no way to give a sprite a Y coord of -1 (or lesS)... so no sprites should ever be found in-range on the prerender scanline.</div>

