				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">- Here! During the sprite CHR fetches (from PPU $1000, so A12=1), the loopy_v A12 is zero, causing multiple IRQ clocks. It's mostly 1,0,1,0,1,0... because the first rising (due to sprite CHR fetch) occurs at PPU cc 260; but at cycle 263, A12=0 because loopy_v A12 is zero.
<br />
<br />- In other words, CPU A12 (loopy_v) is zero, while PPU A12 (chr fetches) is 1.   This way, it's happening a 1,0,1,0... every 3 PPU cc, making the IRQ to clock more than 1 time per scanline.
<br />
<br />- Any help?</div>

